    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if mechanical tension is the main thing, does that mean i should just focus on low reps and heavy weights all the time? or is there a point where the metabolic stress part actually becomes more effective for muscle size?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Focusing *only* on heavy weights and low reps is a solid strategy, but you can't ignore the other side of the coin, or you'll end up with a muscle that's just tough, not necessarily big. You need both the heavy *and* the burn, or you'll just be training your muscles like a rusty old iron door—it might resist, but it won't really *grow*. A good training program needs to cycle between those two stimuli, making sure you hit both the tension and the metabolic stress points.",
      "source": "target",
